-----------ALGO WITH Example-------------
Algorithm: Count Inversions using Merge Sort

Input: Array arr of size n
Output: Number of inversions in the array

Step 1: Define function mergeSort(arr, low, high)
    1.1 If low >= high:
            return 0

    1.2 Find mid = (low + high) // 2

    1.3 Recursively count inversions in left half:
            leftCount = mergeSort(arr, low, mid)

    1.4 Recursively count inversions in right half:
            rightCount = mergeSort(arr, mid + 1, high)

    1.5 Count inversions while merging:
            mergeCount = merge(arr, low, mid, high)

    1.6 Return total inversions:
            return leftCount + rightCount + mergeCount


Step 2: Define function merge(arr, low, mid, high)
    2.1 Initialize:
            temp = empty list
            left = low
            right = mid + 1
            count = 0

    2.2 While left <= mid AND right <= high:
            If arr[left] <= arr[right]:
                append arr[left] to temp
                left += 1
            Else:
                append arr[right] to temp
                count += (mid - left + 1)
                right += 1

    2.3 Copy remaining elements from left half (if any)

    2.4 Copy remaining elements from right half (if any)

    2.5 Copy temp back into arr[low...high]

    2.6 Return count


Step 3: Call mergeSort(arr, 0, n-1)
